cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.MM

The paper focuses on the problem of optimizing human perception in the context of motion planning for VR telepresence, which involves both human-computer interaction (HCI) and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also proposes a multiobjective optimization framework and uses an A* type method for trajectory planning, which falls under the categories of cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.GR (Graphics). Additionally, the paper involves processing and analyzing 360 video, which could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
